\section{Detailed CPI Flow Architecture}
\label{sec:cpi-flows}

\subsection{Critical Cross-Program Invocation Flows}

GridTokenX implements three primary CPI patterns that enable composable business logic across program boundaries, as illustrated in Fig.~\ref{fig:cpi-flows}.

\begin{figure}[htbp]
\centering
\resizebox{\columnwidth}{!}{%
\begin{tikzpicture}[
    node distance=0.6cm and 0.8cm,
    program/.style={rectangle, draw, rounded corners, minimum width=1.5cm, minimum height=0.55cm, align=center, font=\scriptsize},
    arrow/.style={->, >=stealth, thick, font=\tiny}
]
% Flow 1: Settlement
\node[program, fill=blue!15] (reg1) {Registry};
\node[program, fill=green!15, right=1.5cm of reg1] (et1) {Energy Token};
\node[program, fill=yellow!15, right=1.5cm of et1] (spl1) {SPL Token-2022};
\draw[arrow] (reg1) -- (et1) node[midway, above] {settle};
\draw[arrow] (et1) -- (spl1) node[midway, above] {mint};

% Flow 2: ERC Verification
\node[program, fill=orange!15, below=1cm of reg1] (gov2) {Governance};
\node[program, fill=blue!15, right=1.5cm of gov2] (reg2) {Registry};
\draw[arrow] (gov2) -- (reg2) node[midway, above] {verify};

% Flow 3: Trading Validation
\node[program, fill=red!15, below=1cm of gov2] (trd3) {Trading};
\node[program, fill=orange!15, right=1.5cm of trd3] (gov3) {Governance};
\draw[arrow] (trd3) -- (gov3) node[midway, above] {validate};

% Labels
\node[left=0.2cm of reg1, font=\tiny\itshape] {Flow 1};
\node[left=0.2cm of gov2, font=\tiny\itshape] {Flow 2};
\node[left=0.2cm of trd3, font=\tiny\itshape] {Flow 3};
\end{tikzpicture}}%
\caption{Primary CPI Flow Patterns Between Anchor Programs}
\label{fig:cpi-flows}
\end{figure}

\subsubsection{Energy Settlement to Token Minting}

The Registry program settles energy balances and invokes Energy Token minting via CPI:

\smallskip
\noindent\texttt{Registry.settle\_energy()} $\xrightarrow{\text{CPI}}$ \texttt{EnergyToken.mint\_tokens\_direct()}
\smallskip

\textbf{Flow Details}:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Registry calculates unsettled energy: $unsettled = net\_gen - settled\_net\_gen$
    \item Registry CPI to Energy Token with settlement proof
    \item Energy Token verifies PDA authority
    \item SPL Token-2022 mint invoked with PDA signer seeds
    \item Registry updates settled\_net\_generation high-water mark
    \item Atomic operation: both succeed or both fail
\end{enumerate}

\textbf{Cost}: 12,000 CU total (3,500 CU registry + 8,500 CU cross-program)

\subsubsection{ERC Issuance with Double-Claim Verification}

The Governance program prevents duplicate claims by verifying with Registry:

\smallskip
\noindent\texttt{Governance.issue\_erc\_with\_verification()}\\
$\xrightarrow{\text{CPI}}$ \texttt{Registry.verify\_unclaimed\_energy()}
\smallskip

\textbf{Flow Details}:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Governance initiates ERC issuance for claimed energy amount
    \item CPI to Registry to verify energy not already tokenized
    \item Registry checks: claimed\_erc\_generation + requested $\leq$ settled\_net\_gen
    \item Registry updates claimed\_erc\_generation high-water mark
    \item Governance mints ERC certificate upon verification
    \item Dual high-water mark enforcement prevents double-spending
\end{enumerate}

\textbf{Cost}: 11,200 CU (6,500 CU governance + 4,700 CU verification)

\subsubsection{Trading with ERC Validation}

The Trading program validates ERC certificates before order acceptance:

\smallskip
\noindent\texttt{Trading.create\_sell\_order()} $\xrightarrow{\text{CPI}}$ \texttt{Governance.validate\_erc()}
\smallskip

\textbf{Flow Details}:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Seller creates order with optional ERC certificate ID
    \item Trading CPI to Governance for ERC validation
    \item Governance verifies certificate status (Active/Valid)
    \item Premium pricing applied for renewable-backed orders
    \item Order created with ERC\_linked flag upon validation
\end{enumerate}

\textbf{Cost}: 9,800 CU (7,500 CU trading + 2,300 CU validation)

\subsection{CPI Account Pattern}

All CPI implementations follow a standard account structure:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{CPI Accounts}: Define AccountInfo references for target program
    \item \textbf{CPI Context}: Create with target program and accounts
    \item \textbf{Signer Seeds}: Optional PDA seeds for program signing
    \item \textbf{Invocation}: Call target program instruction with CPI context
\end{itemize}

\section{Event Structure Specifications}
\label{sec:events}

\subsection{Event Emission Architecture}

All state changes emit structured events for off-chain indexing and audit trails.

\subsection{Core Event Types}

