\caption{GridTokenX Event Specifications}
\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{lp{5.5cm}p{4cm}}
\toprule
\textbf{Event} & \textbf{Fields} & \textbf{Purpose} \\
\midrule
SellOrderCreated & seller, order\_id, amount, price, timestamp & Order book indexing \\
BuyOrderCreated & buyer, order\_id, amount, price, timestamp & Order book indexing \\
OrderMatched & buy\_order, sell\_order, amount, price, timestamp & Trade settlement log \\
\midrule
TokensMinted & recipient, amount, meter\_reading\_id, timestamp & Token supply tracking \\
TokensBurned & owner, amount, reason, timestamp & Token destruction log \\
\midrule
MeterReadingSubmitted & meter\_id, production, consumption, timestamp & Oracle data feed \\
MeterReadingValidated & meter\_id, status, quality\_score, timestamp & Quality assurance \\
\midrule
UserRegistered & user\_pubkey, user\_type, geolocation, timestamp & Identity registry \\
MeterRegistered & meter\_id, owner, meter\_type, zone\_id, timestamp & Device registry \\
\midrule
ERCIssued & certificate\_id, owner, energy\_amount, source, timestamp & Certificate creation \\
ERCValidated & certificate\_id, validator, status, timestamp & Trading approval \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\label{tab:events}
\end{center}
\end{table*}

\subsection{Event Indexing}

Events are consumed by off-chain services for:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{PostgreSQL Storage}: Persistent audit trail with foreign key relationships
    \item \textbf{WebSocket Broadcast}: Real-time updates to connected clients
    \item \textbf{Analytics Pipeline}: Time-series aggregation for market insights
    \item \textbf{Compliance Reporting}: Regulatory audit trail generation
\end{itemize}

